criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        • Healthy university students of both genders with normal mobility of the joints of the
        upper quadrant of the body.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Deformities in the upper quadrant region of the body;

          -  Complaints in this region in the last 6 months;

          -  Surgical procedures or musculoskeletal, cardiac, renal, metabolic, neurological and or
             oncological pathologies of the upper quadrant that may disturb nerve function;

          -  Not present any mechanosensitive response to ULNT1;

          -  Pregnant women;

          -  Ingestion of non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs or consumption of any type of
             narcotic drugs and participants who have drunk alcohol in the last 12 hours.
